.SH NAME
SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_WHEEL_DEVICES_EXCLUDED \- A variable containing a list of devices that are not wheel style controllers\[char46]
.SH HEADER FILE
Defined in SDL3/SDL_hints\[char46]h

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "#define SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_WHEEL_DEVICES_EXCLUDED "SDL_JOYSTICK_WHEEL_DEVICES_EXCLUDED"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
This will override

.BR SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_WHEEL_DEVICES
 and the
built in device list\[char46]

The format of the string is a comma separated list of USB VID/PID pairs in
hexadecimal form, e\[char46]g\[char46]
.BR 0xAAAA/0xBBBB,0xCCCC/0xDDDD
The variable can also take the form of "@file", in which case the named
file will be loaded and interpreted as the value of the variable\[char46]

This hint can be set anytime\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This hint is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

